    <item>
      <title>Prefer simple methods</title>
      <link>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/prefer-short-methods/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 18 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/prefer-short-methods/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://alexkval.github.io/posts/prefer-short-methods&#34;&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://alexkval.github.io/posts/prefer-short-methods/code.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;screenshot&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Long methods vs simple ones. What&amp;rsquo;s the problem?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Long methods&amp;rsquo; issues:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;usually does too much and &amp;ldquo;knows&amp;rdquo; too much&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;as a consequence, it breaks the Single Responsibility Principle&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;it is harder to grasp what it does when you read it&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;more changes needed to add or amend functionality&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;you have to write pretty complex tests&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;and you need a lot of them to cover all of the possible permutations&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Exception vs StandardError</title>
      <link>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/exception-vs-standard-error/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 26 Jan 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/exception-vs-standard-error/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-rb&#34; data-lang=&#34;rb&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# RuntimeError &amp;lt; StandardError &amp;lt; Exception &amp;lt; Object&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  require &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;does/not/exist&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;Exception&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; e&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;it is an Exception&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# =&amp;gt; &amp;#34;it is an Exception&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  require &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;does/not/exist&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;StandardError&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; e&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;it is an Exception&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;# =&amp;gt; LoadError: cannot load such file -- does/not/exist&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;What is the difference in results between this&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-rb&#34; data-lang=&#34;rb&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;raise&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Oups&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Hi&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;and this?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-rb&#34; data-lang=&#34;rb&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;require &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;does/not/exist&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;rescue&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Hi&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;And why the results are different. Let&amp;rsquo;s figure it out step by step.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>JavaScript-like HashMaps in Ruby</title>
      <link>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/js-like-hashmap-in-ruby/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 06 Jul 2020 14:36:17 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>https://alexkval.github.io/posts/js-like-hashmap-in-ruby/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://alexkval.github.io/posts/js-like-hashmap-in-ruby/intro.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;screenshot&#34; title=&#34;Photo by Joshua Aragon on Unsplash&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In the previous &lt;a href=&#34;https://alexkval.github.io/posts/js-like-object-in-rails/&#34;&gt;JavaScript like object in Ruby on Rails&lt;/a&gt; article,&#xA;I&amp;rsquo;ve described how similar behavior can be achieved in Rails code.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;But in pure Ruby there still is no short way for this.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It turns out that a proposal to Ruby core has been made to add this nice-to-have feature.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
